Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Halve, peel, and mince half the @shallot{1}(minced) (save the rest for
another use; for 4 servings, mince whole shallot).

In a small #pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for
4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and
reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered
off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, toss @green beans{6%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle
of oil, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender,
~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season all over
with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a large
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked
through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a
#cutting board{} and set aside to rest. Wipe out pan.

Add shallot, @thyme{1/4%ounce} sprigs, and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} to
same pan over medium heat. Cook, stirring, until shallot is softened,
~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @apricot jam{2%tbsp} and @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} (use all
the vinegar for 4 servings). Let simmer until syrupy, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in
@chicken stock concentrate{1} and 1/4 cup water (1/3 cup for 4). Simmer until
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4)
until melted.

> Stir in a splash of water if sauce seems thick.

Remove thyme sprigs from pan and discard. Season sauce with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Fluff rice with a fork; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Thinly
slice chicken; divide between plates with rice and green beans. Drizzle chicken
with sauce and serve.